3 threatened future releases, or preventing or limiting human, environmental, or natural resource exposure to
4 previous petroleum, petroleum product, or hazardous substance releases. The term may include limiting access
5 to the property, monitoring known contaminants, and complying with state, local, or both state and local
6 requirements.
7 (j) "Responsible party" means:
8 (i) a person responsible for conducting the assessment, investigation, and cleanup at a brownfield
9 site as determined through:
10 (A) a judgment rendered in a court of law or an administrative order;
11 (B) an enforcement action by federal authorities or the department; or
